My hubs and I and our two sweet snuggly little pups visited Washington DC, specifically, the Georgetown area this morning. After going in a nice walk, we decided to grab some brunch/breakfast. We found the Peacock Cafe. We were instantly impressed with the lovely servers dressed to the nines! The servers even brought water to our baby pups. I enjoyed the Chesapeake Eggs Benny, with real crab. My hubby enjoyed his hash. I also had the Bellini, which tasted like a mimosa. And I had the Peacock coffee, which was heavy on the liquor- but I’m not complaining!

I found this place last minute as a spot where we could grab a bite and take our dog, Cooper. I wasn’t expecting much since it was such a last minute find, but I really enjoyed everything about Peacock Café!  My dad and I split the calamari as an appetizer and we really enjoyed it! It’s the perfect size to split between two hungry guys. I ended up getting the grilled chicken as my entree and I was thoroughly impressed! It was moist and tender throughout, and the fries made a great pair!  As far as my dog’s experience goes, I’m sure he had a blast! Our waiter kindly provided Cooper (our dog) with a water bowl which he desperately needed after his walk around DC. Cooper also got to taste some really great calamari and chicken (not from the table, of course).  I’d 100% give this place a try! The patio seating is comfortable and serene. The food is great and so is the service!

The Peacock Café has become my go-to place for Sunday brunch when visiting DC. If you can’t find a Reservation, but are in the area, I recommend stopping by. They try to accommodate you. And if there’s a wait, there’s a great bar or there are a number of nice shops near by.  The service is great. The wait staff is really attentive. Yesterday I asked if the fries were GF (they are but use a shared frier, a no-go for me) and three people stopped over to offer suggestions/help. The Gluten Free French toast is always light and delicious. It’s served with warm maple syrup and drenched bananas. They also have a number of fresh juice smoothies to choose from.

I recently went to the Peacock Cafe for lunch. I ordered the bison burger which arrived in a timely manner. All was well until I bit into the burger and found a hair in between the lettuce and bun. After showing this to the management they brought me a new burger and apologized for the inconvenience and assured me I would not be charged for the burger. Once I received the bill and saw the burger was on the check I asked the manager why and her response was “we charged you for the burger without the hair”. After explaining to her that they almost fed me a hair she then proceeded to insinuate that I placed the hair there myself.... The argument then proceeded and she eventually removed the charge. Afterwards,  the family beside us left before ordering because they overheard the conversation about the hair and were shocked at the managements accusations and handling of the situation. Needless to say I will not be returning.

My dining experience at this restaurant was nothing short of phenomenal! Initially I was unimpressed; the decor could use some rethinking to create a cozier environment, the bathroom was dusty, a little bit messy and the ceiling looked like it had been swollen from a leak and wasn't gonna hold much longer🤔😒...... BUT! ..... The FOOD WAS REMARKABLE.😍 The presentation, mixture of flavors, attention to detail by the kitchen left nothing to be desired! I got the 3course meal special (which has an appetizer,meal, desert and even includes gratuity!) [Also shown are a chicken rigatoni and a seafood jambalaya] My choices were watermelon salad, mushroom risotto, and duo sorbet. All I can say about my meal is that my taste buds we're in heaven! Finding truly FRESH fruit is always a struggle for me when it comes to eating at restaurants, so 2 thumbs way up to Peacock Cafe for doing it right!! The fruit in the salad was crisp, juicy and sweet, (a fruit lovers trifecta) and topped with Feta cheese. OMG I could it this all day😊😋!! The mushroom risotto tasted like... Well, mushroom risotto! It had a rich yet subtle flavor of all things mushroom and I love mushrooms, (another struggle of mine when eating out) but once again, Peacock Cafe got it right! The sorbet was rich and creamy and the flavors weren't too overpowering, it was a lovely retreat for my mouth after such a delectable meal! This place has great choices for meat lovers, and veggie lovers alike. Drink menu is also extensive and includes something for everyone's palate. I ordered a glass of Lemoncello, (my first time having) and I can understand why the glass was not delivered full. The drink tasted as potent and lemony as it smelled. But I cannot dispute the freshness of this item either! This place gets 5 stars from me and I'm picky. I appreciate the attention the kitchen paid to the little things, it warmed this food lover's heart... And I am not easy to please!

First time eating there, I have to say their food was excellent, fresh and so tasty. The only other time I had Mediterranean  Bronzino's so fresh on this side of Atlantic was at Eataly NYC Flatiron. Staff were professional and friendly, definitely a must if you are in Georgetown and want to have a great night.

I ate here for brunch on Sunday. I had a reservation and would recommend you make one too - the place was quite busy. Wait staff were friendly and professional. The grapefruit cocktail was strong but well blended. The eggs on the eggs benedict chesapeake were semi-runny and slightly salted. The only boring item was the peacock fries; an unnecessarily large portion of thin cut fries with no additional seasoning. I would recommend you order a different side in lieu of the fries.
I love the shakes and juices for brunch! And the food is good.

I wasn't that impressed. Bloody Mary was average. Not particularly good service or friendly. Felt like they wanted to get us out to get another brunch sitting in. Personally I much preferred Tonic for brunch on the GWU campus. The staff were much friendlier, it was more chilled and I thought a nicer setting
Food was pretty mediocre. I'm vegetarian so I ordered a pasta dish that was somehow worse than something I could have made at home. Obviously can't attest to how the meat dishes are.
Excellent Persian Kabob sreved for Nowruz!
Great food, and great service! Lively place, but not too noisy that you can't hold a decent conversation with your friends.
This place has a high class atmosphere I love. Go here for dinner, dressed well, and your experience will be complete.  The servers are pleasant and helpful. The food is great. The drinks are great.
Luxury restaurant with superb ambiance.  Best georgetown restaurant with amazing Roasted Salmon. Definitely suggest that.
Very nice coffee and breakfast place. The selection for vegetarians was a bit small.
Great food. Great atmosphere. Great brunch.
Nothing special, but not a bad choice if looking for a spot off Wisconsin
Pancakes
Good Food, Good Place.
Went for brunch and it's overpriced for what it is.  I had the egg whites omelet and it was okay.  The biscuit was probably the best thing on my plate.
Quite good.
Just perfect. Dining here it is like dining at my home with my family. Loved it.
Unlike the rest of DC they keep it simple and real! Awesome wine and spirits selection.
It's a 3.5. The Fresh juices/smoothies are delicious. However the brunch is not to die for and is very expensive for what it is. Positive highlight : food is organic
Love It!
Great service, great food and quaint fashionable atmosphere.
Always friendly and accommodating. Food is fantastic and they serve brunch items till 4:00pm!

Everything at this cafe is amazing. Literally, everything. Even down to the coffee and their bread. The environment that they set up in the restaurant is classy and chic. I came here to with family and the food was so full of flavor with every bite, and worth every penny. I've honestly never been to a place with such an interesting new variety on their menu. The owner even came by to see how we were doing, thanked us for coming, and was truly very kind. I highly recommend this place, as well as their calamari, and their rigatoni. Never had better.

I have been to Peacock Cafe numerous times recently. My table was served by server named Ramon. The service has been excellent and the food has come the way I wanted. I could not ask for anything more. Also the server also has suggested somethings which made my day. I would go back more often for same food and also juices.

I've been a regular at Peacock Cafe for over a decade (previously with friends, now with my husband) and it never fails to be a wonderful experience. Every item is prepared fresh from high-quality ingredients, and the drinks are inventive. To top it off, the staff are all welcoming, no matter if you're dressed for a night out or in jeans & a t-shirt. Location's perfect, price is reasonable, and parking is plentiful. You can't go wrong with Peacock Cafe!

Used to come here every Friday for lunch with friends.  The staff is excellent and the owners know most of their patrons by name.  My favorite item is the SW BLT, their fries are super tasty and the Sauv Blanc is best enjoyed on their world famous patio.
Do you wear boat shoes and pastels? This is your jam. Also, the salad with grilled chicken is great.

I enjoyed having brunch here one Sunday morning. The place prides itself on fresh juices. I had a Red Zinger, which was made from apple, carrot, beet, and ginger. It is an easy combination to screw up, but they made it very well and promptly. The owner visited our table and said hello to seemingly everyone of the throng who was there. The coffee was good, as was the salmon omelet. I look forward to returning. (Visited 3/9/14)
Excellent!
An amazing place with an incredible menu!

A restaurant that is good for virtually every meal. The prices are great, the quality of food is excellent, and the service is outstanding. The owners have done a great job creating a happy and sophisticated atmosphere. The location makes this a great place to start a sunday stroll around georgetown. Definitely my go-to-spot.
My favorite Georgetown place, by far.  The welcoming owners have been on that block for years and have developed a truly "Georgetown Place'.

I will never understand why Peacock Cafe gets all the hype it does. So it's in Georgetown. So what? The people watching is the same as it is down any other side street... nonexistent. For years I've failed to understand how Peacock merits any attention, or furthermore, how it remains in business. Food is average at best and horribly overpriced. Service is overburdened and slow. Worst still, you're made to feel as if you should feel privileged to dine here. For mediocre food and lacking ambiance? Come again? Avoid the lobster roll -- you'll just leave angry.
Small plates are delicious and a nice way to sample some delicious offerings. Nice patio out front.
Good weekend brunch, lovely outdoor patio. The steak and eggs is particularly good.
Sitting outside and relaxing was great. The food and service, not so much.
Very nice, kid-friendly restaurant. We did new years eve dinner and we every happy with the food selection and service.
peacock cafe is nicer for lunch than for dinner - they have a good selection of healthy choices and salads served in a nice atmosphere.  another great place to eat outside during the nice weather.
